==English==
===Etymology===
The word is derived from the Greek "bathos", meaning "[[depth]]", and "phobos", meaning "fear".

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-əʊbiə|-əʊbiə]]

===Noun===
'''bathophobia'''

# The a [[fear]] of deeply dimensioned [[volume]]s such as [[lake]]s or long [[hallway]]s.
#[[fear]] of [[depth]]s

